<title type="html"><![CDATA[&quot;Auto resize all columns width&quot; button]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4596&amp;p=19270#p19270"><![CDATA[
While in &quot;Details&quot; view in Windows 8.1 there's a button on View tab of the Ribbon, that auto resizes all columns width to fit content.<br />I didn't find button with the same function in Classic Explorer options.<br />There are several ways to make this without a button:<br /><ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>by pressing &quot;Ctrl&quot; and &quot;+&quot; (Ctrl and the plus key)</li><li>by right clicking the top line of details and selecting &quot;resize all columns width&quot;</li><li>by double clicking the border of needed columns (this works only for one column)</li></ol>But the button in Classic Explorer Bar would make it much more convenient.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3010">CropperHoff</a> — Tue May 05, 2015 9:38 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
